VGA ball Linux driver and userspace demo

This software package now matches a position-controlled VGA ball peripheral.

Register map expected by the hardware:
- offset 0: ball_x[7:0]
- offset 1: ball_x[9:8] in bits [1:0]
- offset 2: ball_y[7:0]
- offset 3: ball_y[9:8] in bits [1:0]

Userspace interface:
- `VGA_BALL_WRITE_POSITION` writes the ball center `(x, y)`
- `VGA_BALL_READ_POSITION` reads back the last programmed center `(x, y)`

Build:
- `make`

Run on the target board:
- `insmod vga_ball.ko`
- `./hello`
- `rmmod vga_ball`

Notes for the hardware portion of the lab:
- Update `vga_ball.sv` so it implements the register map above.
- Latch the programmed coordinates only during non-visible video time to avoid tearing.
- Record the Slow 1100 mV, 85 C conservative `Fmax` from Quartus and confirm it is above 50 MHz.
